{{Infobox oil refinery | name = Catlettsburg Refinery | image = | image alt = <!-- See WP:Alternative text for images --> | caption = | location_map = Kentucky | location_map_width = | location_map_text = Location of the Catlettsburg Refinery in Kentucky | coordinates = {{coord|38|22|27|N|82|35|55|W|type:landmark_region:US-KY|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = United States | province = [[Kentucky]] | city = [[Catlettsburg, Kentucky]] | operator = | owner = [[Marathon Petroleum Corporation]] | founded = {{Start date|1922}} | closure = | capacity = | capacity bbl/d = 277000 | employees = 775 | contractors = 800 | ref units = | oil tank = | oil refining center = }}
[[File:CatlettsburgRefineryUS23.jpg|thumb|Catlettsburg Refinery]] The '''Catlettsburg Refinery''' is an [[United States|American]] [[oil refinery]]. It is located in northeastern [[Kentucky]], at the intersection of [[Interstate 64]] and [[U.S. Route 23]] in [[Catlettsburg, Kentucky]] near the cities of [[Ashland, Kentucky]] and [[Huntington, West Virginia]]. The facility was built in 1916 by the [[Great Eastern Refining Company]] and purchased in 1924 by the [[Ashland Inc.|Ashland Refining Company]]. The refinery now occupies a {{convert|650|acre|ha|adj=on}} plus site, producing more than {{convert|277000|oilbbl/d|m3/d}}, and employing around 1,600 employees and contractors. Its location on the west banks of the [[Big Sandy River (Ohio River)|Big Sandy River]] and only two miles south of the [[Ohio River]], allows it to ship products by barge as well as pipeline.<ref name="catref">[http://www.marathonpetroleum.com/content/documents/fact_sheets/2014_Catlettsburg_RFS.pdf Catlettsburg Refining, LLC: Catlettsburg, Kentucky] Retrieved on 2014-06-05</ref> It is owned and operated by [[Marathon Petroleum|Marathon Petroleum Corporation]].<ref name="catref"/>
Due to the [[coal mining]] industry and the large quantity of [[petroleum]] products shipped from the refinery, the [[Port of Huntington Tri-State]] is the largest inland port in the [[United States]], with 76.5 million tons shipped in 2007.<ref name="largest">{{cite news|url=http://www.herald-dispatch.com/specialsections/progress4/x1578951257/No-Headline|title=Port of Huntington one of nation's largest.|last=Johnson|first=Curtis|date=March 29, 2009|work=[[Huntington Herald-Dispatch]]|accessdate=2010-02-22}}</ref>
