The '''1795 Sydney Tornado''' was the [[List of Southern Hemisphere tornadoes and tornado outbreaks|first tornado ever recorded in Australia]]. The tornado caused damage to crops and land in the early settlement. Little is known about the event as people didn't have many supplies during early colonization nor significant technology to record data.<ref>http://www.thecourier.com.au/story/1389432/multimedia-tornadoes-in-australia/interactive/</ref>

